Class Summary
AssetDecreaseDocument The Endowment Asset Decrease (EAD) is used to reduce the holdings of a KEMID, either through the cash sale of an asset or by removing it directly from the KEMID holding record.
AssetIncreaseDocument The Endowment Asset Increase (EAI) transaction is used to add to the holdings of a KEMID, either through the cash purchase of an asset or by depositing it directly into the KEMID holding record.
